         <abstract id="aspace_aee75e57eacdca5c8f7d49b1b7fc803c">Correspondence, financial, legal, and other documents of William W. Starr relating to harbor maintenance and improvements in Bridgeport and Norwalk, Connecticut. Included are contracts with the U.S. Army Engineer's Office for work on the harbors, receipts for material and labor, notes on harbor maintenance, clippings, and printed matter.</abstract>
         <origination label="Creator">
            <persname source="local">
               <part localtype="agent_person">Starr, William W.</part>
            </persname>
         </origination>
      </did>
      <acqinfo id="aspace_9262aad563a74b346e0b9f29ccc328a5">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>Gift of William I. Starr, 1945.</p>
      </acqinfo>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_82abf1fa94d930954e07f00feaeed0c8">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>
      </accessrestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_bd60c1277ddbefc978d5abe6a1d5c8e7">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>William W. Starr, Jr. Papers. Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>
      </prefercite>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_0e240330548edc2428176c8524ec017f">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>Correspondence of William W. Starr and others, and related documents, all dealing with harbor maintenance and improvements in Bridgeport and Norwalk, Connecticut, make up the William W. Starr Papers. Many of the papers originate with the Engineer's Office of the United States Army. Included are contracts with the Army for work on the harbors, a petition concerning dredging, receipts for material and labor, notes on harbor maintenance, clippings and printed matter.</p>
      </scopecontent>
